      "content": "Ignoring social safety nets while prioritizing debt is a short-sighted gamble that ignores the real economic engine of a nation. Strong social programs function as automatic stabilizers, preventing massive economic collapses during downturns. A stable, healthy populace is the foundation of a strong economy, and neglecting it guarantees future instability that debt reduction alone cannot fix. Therefore, a balanced approach that ensures essential services while managing debt is the only responsible path.",
