      "content": "The core issue is that the *scale* of the debt matters; an unsustainable debt load is a guaranteed disaster. While social programs are vital, they must be funded sustainably, not by perpetual borrowing. A responsible path requires fiscal discipline to control the debt while making targeted, efficient investments in safety nets, not simply throwing money at every perceived need. The true gamble is allowing unchecked debt to cripple future generations' ability to fund anything at all.",
